---
const diy = [
  '20–40 hours learning config files, integrations, and troubleshooting',
  'Days lost to cryptic error messages and dead-end documentation',
  'Wrong model choices that waste money or underperform',
  'Security gaps you won\'t know about until it\'s too late',
  'Trial and error on prompts that should just work',
  'No one to ask when it breaks at 2am',
];

const expert = [
  'Production-ready in 90 minutes, not weeks',
  'Every integration done right the first time',
  'Model selection optimized for your budget and use cases',
  'Security locked down from day one',
  'Battle-tested prompts tailored to your business',
  'Someone who\'s solved every problem you\'ll hit',
];
---

<section class="section-pad border-t border-white/5">
  <div class="container-md">
    <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Why Consulting</p>
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 max-w-2xl">
      DIY vs. Expert Setup
    </h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-14 max-w-xl">
      OpenClaw is powerful. But the gap between "it's installed" and "it transforms how I work" is configuration, prompt engineering, and knowing what to connect.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- DIY -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/5 bg-surface2 p-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-6 text-neutral-300">Doing It Yourself</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          {diy.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
              <span class="text-neutral-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-base">✕</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Expert -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-6 text-white">Working With Me</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          {expert.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-300">
              <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-base">✓</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Pull quote -->
    <p class="mt-10 text-center text-neutral-500 text-sm max-w-xl mx-auto">
      The real cost isn't the consulting fee. It's the 40 hours you'll spend reinventing solutions I've already built.
      <span class="text-neutral-300 font-medium"> Your time is worth more than that.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
